Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 8-1-42.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]:
4 Chapter 42.5. Community Energy Facilities
5 Sec. 1. The definitions in IC 8-1-40 apply throughout this
6 chapter.
7 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "community energy facility"
8 means a facility:
9 (1) that generates electricity;
10 (2) that is located on a single parcel of land;
11 (3) that is interconnected to the electric distribution grid;
12 (4) to which at least three (3) persons located in the electricity
13 supplier service area in which the facility is located have
14 entered into a subscription;
15 (5) in which at least sixty percent (60%) of the generating
16 capacity is allocated to subscriptions of twenty-five (25)
17 kilowatts or less; and
2026 IN 196—LS 6591/DI 150

2
1 (6) that is designed to offset the energy use of a specified set of
2 subscribers, with no single subscriber having more than a
3 twenty percent (20%) interest in the facility.
4 Sec. 3. (a) As used in this chapter, "community energy facility
5 organization" means an organization whose purpose is to
6 beneficially own and operate a community energy facility for the
7 subscribers to the community energy facility.
8 (b) A community energy facility organization may be a
9 for-profit, nonprofit, cooperative, or governmental entity
10 authorized by Indiana law.
11 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "disadvantaged business
12 enterprise" has the meaning set forth in IC 5-16-6.5-1.
13 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "low or moderate income" means
14 an individual or household income of not more than eighty percent
15 (80%) of the area median income based on United States
16 Department of Housing and Urban Development guidelines.
17 Sec. 6. As used in this chapter, "nameplate capacity" has the
18 meaning set forth in 170 IAC 4-4.2-1.
19 Sec. 7. As used in this chapter, "subscribing customer" means
20 a retail customer of an electricity supplier that enters into one (1)
21 or more subscriptions with one (1) or more community energy
22 facilities.
23 Sec. 8. As used in this chapter, "subscription" means a contract
24 between a subscriber and a community energy facility
25 organization.
26 Sec. 9. Not later than one hundred eighty (180) days after the
27 commission adopts rules under section 14 of this chapter, an
28 electricity supplier shall begin:
29 (1) allowing interconnection with the electricity supplier's
30 facilities by community energy facilities; and
31 (2) providing bill credits under section 10 of this chapter to
32 subscribing customers of the electricity supplier.
33 Sec. 10. (a) A community energy facility organization that
34 operates a community energy facility that is interconnected with
35 the facilities of an electricity supplier shall, not later than the
36 fifteenth day of each month, transmit to the electricity supplier a
37 report providing the following information:
38 (1) An updated list of subscribers to the community energy
39 facility in the immediately preceding month.
40 (2) The proportional output of the community energy facility
41 attributable to the subscription of each subscriber identified
42 under subdivision (1), calculated as follows:
2026 IN 196—LS 6591/DI 150

3
1 (A) If the subscriber subscribed to receive a specified
2 amount of electricity from the community energy facility
3 during the immediately preceding month, the subscriber's
4 subscription amount is the amount of electricity the
5 subscriber subscribed to receive from the community
6 energy facility during the immediately preceding month.
7 (B) If the subscriber subscribed to receive a specified
8 proportion of the community energy facility's generated
9 electricity in the immediately preceding month, the
10 subscriber's subscription amount equals:
11 (i) the proportion of the community energy facility's
12 generated electricity the subscriber subscribed to receive
13 in the immediately preceding month; multiplied by
14 (ii) the total amount of electricity generated by the
15 community energy facility in the immediately preceding
16 month.
17 (b) An electricity supplier shall provide to a subscribing
18 customer a credit on the subscribing customer's electricity bill for
19 a billing cycle that is equal to:
20 (1) the total subscription amount reported for the subscribing
21 customer by the community energy facility organization
22 under subsection (a)(2) for the billing cycle; multiplied by
23 (2) the applicable community energy credit rate established
24 by the commission in rules adopted by the commission under
25 section 14 of this chapter.
26 If the amount of a bill credit provided to a subscribing customer
27 for a billing cycle exceeds the amount of the subscribing customer's
28 bill for that billing cycle, the electricity supplier shall carry over
29 the amount of the excess in subsequent billing cycles until the full
30 amount of the excess has been credited to the subscribing
31 customer.
32 (c) An electricity supplier shall, not later than the fifteenth day
33 of each month, electronically report the following information to
34 a community energy facility organization that operates a
35 community energy facility that is interconnected with the
36 electricity supplier's facilities:
37 (1) The proportional output of the community energy facility
38 attributable to the subscription of each subscriber to the
39 community energy facility.
40 (2) The bill credit provided to each subscribing customer
41 under subsection (b) for the immediately preceding billing
42 cycle.
2026 IN 196—LS 6591/DI 150

4
1 (3) The applicable community energy credit rate established
2 by the commission in rules adopted by the commission under
3 section 14 of this chapter.
4 (d) An electricity supplier shall provide bill credits under this
5 section to a subscribing customer for the life of the community
6 energy facility to which the customer subscribes.
7 Sec. 11. An electricity supplier may not change the terms of
8 service of a subscribing customer on the basis of the subscribing
9 customer's subscription to a community energy facility.
10 Sec. 12. All environmental attributes of a community energy
11 facility, including renewable energy certificates, are property of
12 the owner of the community energy facility.
13 Sec. 13. A community energy facility is eligible for any incentive
14 programs offered to such facilities under applicable state or federal
15 law.
16 Sec. 14. (a) Not later than July 1, 2027, the commission shall
17 adopt rules under IC 4-22-2 necessary for the administration of
18 this chapter.
19 (b) The rules adopted by the commission under this section
20 must:
21 (1) be consistent with the state policy expressed in
22 IC 8-1-2-0.6;
23 (2) establish the community energy credit rate or rates to be
24 used for purposes of section 10 of this chapter, which must be
25 calculated to:
26 (A) allow for all classes of retail electric customers to
27 realize tangible economic benefits from subscribing to
28 community energy facilities; and
29 (B) create a viable financial market for community energy
30 development;
31 (3) establish uniform fees, standards, and processes for
32 interconnection that:
33 (A) are nondiscriminatory and not unreasonably
34 burdensome for operators of community energy facilities;
35 and
36 (B) allow an electricity supplier to recover reasonable costs
37 of interconnecting the electricity supplier's facilities with
38 a community energy facility;
39 (4) provide for recovery by an electricity supplier of
40 reasonable administrative costs associated with the electricity
41 supplier's provision of bill credits to the electricity supplier's
42 subscribing customers under section 10 of this chapter;
